<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.guncite.com/gun_control_gcgvinco.html">www.guncite.com/gun_contr...vinco.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Similarly, you should also note the wording Sheheban used, &quot;rates for gun deaths.&quot;<br>
<br>
This is an old trick.  He is including gun suicides to paint a worse picture.  The homicide rates for those countries discounting suicides:<br>
<br>
USA : 5.70<br>
<br>
Switzerland : 1.32<br>
<br>
Scotland : 2.24<br>
<br>
England &amp; Wales : 1.41<br>
<br>
Japan : 0.62<br>
<br>
What does this mean?  Switzerland, where 27.2% of houses have guns, has a lower homicide rate than England &amp; Wales with their strict gun control laws.<br>
<br>
An just for the hell of it, when we thow Norway into the mix (with a 32% household with gun rate), the picture becomes even more iteresting.  Their homicide rate is at 0.97.<br>
<br>
It was a nice try though, Sheheban.<br>
