<br>
If this is true, which seems almost common sense (murder rates are always highest in large cities, right?), then maybe the gun restriction nuts should be focusing on violent murders per usable population density (not total density, of course, since 90% of the US is &quot;wasted space&quot;). I suspect that will have a much larger influence on what the violent crime numbers mean than how tough a country's gun control laws are.<br>
<br>
